message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Haiti in the past 5 years was the assassination of President Jovenel Moïse. On July 7, 2021, Moïse was killed during an attack on his residence in Port-au-Prince. This event shocked the nation and created political chaos and instability in Haiti. It led to a power vacuum and heightened tensions within the country, deepening the existing social, economic, and political crises. The assassination of President Moïse has had far-reaching consequences for Haiti's governance, security, and future trajectory.
